<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880128-0080 </DOCNO><HL> Medstat Systems Inc. To Report Profit Rose 10% in Its 1st Quarter </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MDST </CO><IN> CEO </IN><DATELINE> ANN ARBOR, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Medstat Systems Inc. expects to report that earnings rose about 10% for the first quarter ended Dec. 31, Ernest G. Ludy, chairman, president and chief executive officer and Jennifer S. Ponski, vice president and chief financial officer, said.    Revenue rose &quot;between 13% and 14%&quot; to more than $1.4 million, Ms. Ponski said. Revenue in the year-ago period was $1.3 million.    Net income in the latest quarter rose about 10% to more than $325,000 including a tax-loss carry-forward credit, Ms. Ponski said in an interview. Per-share figures should be &quot;up in the same order as our dollar amount for the net income,&quot; she added.    In the fiscal 1987 first quarter, net income was $298,000, or 11 cents a share, including a $122,000 credit for a tax-loss carry-forward. Medstat will announce actual results at its annual meeting tomorrow.    The developer and marketer of medical-cost databases and computer services expects continued growth in the current fiscal year ending Sept. 30. </TEXT></DOC>